'''''Grange Hill''''' is a 1987 [[video game]] published by [[Argus Press Software]] for the [[Commodore 64]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.denofgeek.com/games/revisiting-grange-hill-the-computer-game/|title = Revisiting Grange Hill: The Computer Game|date = 24 May 2018}}</ref> [[ZX Spectrum]],<ref>{{WoS game|id=0002120}}</ref> and [[Amstrad CPC]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.xgd.com/id/44502 |title=Grange Hill for the Commodore 64, XGD.com |access-date=2007-10-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110928075115/http://www.xgd.com/id/44502 |archive-date=2011-09-28 |url-status=dead }}</ref>  It is based on ''[[Grange Hill]]'', a popular children's television show. The music was done by [[David Whittaker (video game composer)|David Whittaker]],<ref name="lemon64" /> but did not include the TV show's theme tune.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://archive.org/details/cvg-magazine-068/page/n92/mode/1up?view=theater|title=CVG Magazine Issue 068|date=June 1987}}</ref>

The Commodore 64 version was coded by Michael Delves.<ref name="lemon64" />

==Plot==
The game's protagonist is Luke "Gonch" Gardener,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.denofgeek.com/games/revisiting-grange-hill-the-computer-game/|title = Revisiting Grange Hill: The Computer Game|date = 24 May 2018}}</ref> with Paul "Hollo" Holloway as an assistant<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://archive.org/details/Computer_Gamer_Issue_25_1987-04_Argus_Press_GB/page/n61/mode/1up?view=theater|title=Computer Gamer - Issue 25 (1987-04)(Argus Press)(GB)|date=April 1987}}</ref> (see the [[List of Grange Hill characters|list of pupils in Grange Hill]]). The object of the game is to retrieve Gonch's [[personal stereo]] from the school<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.denofgeek.com/games/revisiting-grange-hill-the-computer-game/|title = Revisiting Grange Hill: The Computer Game|date = 24 May 2018}}</ref> after hours, which his teacher confiscated.

